{
  "doc_id": "44096",
  "text": "In addition to these 3 major infectious pathogens, an increasing number of new Bartonella spp. have been identified in recent years as zoonotic pathogens transmitted by diverse arthropod vectors [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Currently, >40 official and candidate Bartonella species are listed in the Taxonomy Database of the National Center for Biotechnology Information (http://www.bacterio.net/Bartonella.html); 31 are recognized species. During their evolution, Bartonella lineages have adapted to a variety of hosts and developed virulence factors associated with a diverse set of disease signs and symptoms [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
